label: L.I.E.S.
description:
L.I.E.S. capo Morelli allows for more classic club emotion in his raw disco-house buckers on the label’s 200th release - RIYL Traxx, Daft Punk, Adonis, Legowelt.

Shapeshifting algorithmatists Dane Law and Chants pluck out a sort of AI medieval chamber jazz for the ever unpredictable The Trilogy Tapes.

description:
France’s spellbinding live recording, Do Den Haag Church arrives on a 3rd pressing, but don’t fret if you’ve never heard of it or them; previous copies were only distributed privately between pals and at their live shows, which, combined with the power of their music, has made it quite a collector’s item.

Funnily enough France are french, and their country’s culture of indulgent, communal pleasure is at the core of their three-way jams, played in hypnotically repetitive formation on amped hurdy gurdy... more

Seriously this is the ONE!!!
